headlines.description: Dakota Mathias, Vince Edwards and P.J Thompson combined for 46 first-half points and No. 19 Purdue made 13 of 18 shots from 3-point range before halftime, crushing Fairfield 106-64 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: No. 19 Purdue makes 13 first-half 3s, crushes Fairfield

headlines.description: Corey Davis' putback with 0.3 seconds left gave Houston a 68-66 victory over Liberty on Saturday in a consolation semifinal in the Paradise Jam.
headlines.shortLinkText: Corey Davis' putback wins it for Houston, 68-66

headlines.description: Tyler Wideman scored 19 points, Kamar Baldwin 18, Sean McDermott 17 and Paul Jorgensen 16 as the four players shot a combined 65.8 percent from the floor and Butler beat Furman 82-65 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Butler's big 4 comes through in 82-65 win against Furman

headlines.description: Phlandrous Fleming Jr. knocked down 5 of 7 from 3-point range and scored 19 points to spark Charleston Southern to an 82-72 victory over South Carolina Upstate.
headlines.shortLinkText: Fleming Jr. leads Charleston Southern over SC Upstate 82-72

headlines.description: Jerrick Harding scored 21 points on 7-of-11 shooting and Ryan Richardson hit five 3-pointers and scored 18 to power Weber State to a 73-65 victory over James Madison at the Islands of the Bahamas Showcase on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Harding, Richardson lead Weber St past James Madison 73-65

headlines.description: Isaiah Blackmon scored 18 points, including a go-ahead 3-pointer, Keith Braxton had his 10th career double-double, and St. Francis (Pa.) beat Longwood 83-56 on Saturday to win its first game of the season.
headlines.shortLinkText: St. Francis (Pa.) downs Longwood 83-56 behind Blackmon's 18

headlines.description: Bryson Scott had 14 of his 19 points in the final 6:20 and Fort Wayne pulled away from UIC for a 67-51 win on Saturday.
Kevin McClain made six 3-pointers and scored 27 points and Belmont threw up a school-record 43 shots from the arc before getting past Houston Baptist 93-88 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Belmont puts up 43 from arc, edges Houston Baptist 93-88

headlines.description: Shannon Bogues and TJ Holyfield combined for 55 points as Stephen F. Austin almost doubled Division III Howard Payne's point total for a 118-64 victory on Saturday afternoon.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bogues, Holyfield combine for 55 points, SFA wins 118-64

headlines.description: Arkim Robertson, Khalil Ahmad and Dwight Ramos scored 12 points apiece as CS Fullerton picked up an easy win, beating Bethesda of the NCCAA 77-35 on Saturday afternoon.
Nijal Pearson had 19 points and 11 rebounds and Nedeljko Prijovic added 13 points with nine rebounds to lead Texas State to its first win of the season, beating UT Rio Grande 75-58 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Pearson has 19 points, 11 boards as Texas St. gets 75-58 win

headlines.description: Femi Olujobi set career highs with 37 points and 18 rebounds on Saturday night and North Carolina A&T used a late rally to force overtime and then powered through the extra period for a 90-82 win over Jacksonville.
headlines.shortLinkText: NC A&T beats Jacksonville 90-82 in OT

headlines.description: Daniel Utomi scored 32 points with seven 3-pointers, both career highs, and Akron made 15 of 31 3-pointers in downing UT Martin 76-59 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Akron downs UT Martin 76-59 on Utomi's career night

headlines.description: Isaiah Reese posted the first triple-double in Canisius' 114-year basketball history and the Golden Griffins weathered a second-half run by Youngstown State to win 104-84 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Reese posts Canisius' first triple-double in 104-84 victory

headlines.description: Jordon Talley scored 18 points and had 14 assists to help UNC Wilmington hold off Campbell for an 88-84 victory on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: UNC Wilmington holds off Campbell's late rally, wins 88-84

headlines.description: Nick Griffin hit a 3-point jumper after a scramble for the ball in the final minute to seal a 70-61 victory for Saint Peter's over Sacred Heart on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Griffin scrambles for 3 to secure Saint Peter's 70-61 win

headlines.description: Olin Carter III scored 13 of his 21 points in the first half and San Diego rolled to a 71-62 victory over Norfolk State on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: San Diego jumps out early, cruises past Norfolk State 71-62

headlines.description: Victor Sanders had a key pair of 3s late in the second half and finished with 22 points to help Idaho beat Sam Houston State 63-54 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Sanders helps Idaho late in 63-54 win over Sam Houston State

nowFeed.headline: Under Sean Miller Deandre Ayton is maximizing his enormous potential. Ayton has always possessed the physical tools and a solid basketball IQ. He has worked hard at Zona along with making the adjustments to college basketball. For a freshman big man it's really hard to dominate right away. Since he arrived in the states he was a top ranked player in his class. Would have been top 5 in last years NBA draft. Now he will be a top 3 pick and will be much more prepared.

nowFeed.headline: Cincinnati's loss at Houston will likely drop them from the No. 2-seed line in Joe Lunardi's Bracketology, with Texas Tech likely being the beneficiary to move up. The Cougars, who were a 10-seed coming into the night, scored another big resume win after picking one up over Wichita State in January.
nowFeed.story: Cincinnati's loss at Houston will likely drop them from the No. 2-seed line in Joe Lunardi's Bracketology, with Texas Tech likely being the beneficiary to move up. The Cougars, who were a 10-seed coming into the night, scored another big resume win after picking one up over Wichita State in January.

nowFeed.headline: Houston upsets No. 5 Cincinnati 67-62, ending the Bearcats nation-leading 16-game winning streak. It's the first time the Cougars have beaten two top-10 opponents in a season since 1984.

nowFeed.headline: Ironically, Cincinnati's loss to Houston also finally gives Cincinnati its first win over a likely NCAA Tournament team.
